Involvement is calculated as the weighted sum of the z-scores of players in aerials (15%), defensive actions (25%), touches (40 %) and expected goals buildup (20%), among other players who play the same position.

Involvement tells us how involved players are in the game. It takes into account how often they touch the ball, perform defensive actions, and their participation in aerial duels and attacks that lead to shots.

user: How does involvement differ from touches?
assistant: The metric touches only considers touches on the ball when in possession, whereas involvement also takes into account defensive actions and aerial duels. Furthermore, involvement rewards actions that are part of attacks that end with shots, but the metric touches values all actions equally.
